                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d665">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">715.1715/448: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hanna</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-06-12T18:00:00-05:45"
                            >June 12, 1931—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 13—12:33 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>106. Department’s 111, May 9 [<hi rend="italic">8</hi>], 9 a.m. [<hi
                        rend="italic">5 p.m.</hi>] The Nicaragua-Honduras boundary protocol has been
                    under discussion for some days in the Nicaraguan Congress. The opposition is
                    active and strong in both political parties. President Moncada is in Masaya
                    giving the matter his personal attention and I understand that he is still for
                    approval.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hanna</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
